text: Teshio District in Rumoi and Sōya Subprefecture. is a district divided between Rumoi and Sōya Subprefectures, Hokkaido, Japan. At the end of 2009, the district has an estimated population of 13,937 and an area of 2039.11 km², giving a population density of 6.83 persons per square kilometer. In 2010, the town of Horonobe was transferred from Rumoi Subprefecture to Sōya Subprefecture. ==Towns== ===Rumoi Subprefecture=== *Enbetsu *Teshio ===Sōya Prefecture=== *Horonobe *Toyotomi Category:Districts in Hokkaido
